cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.DS 

This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with recommendation models. The use of resource allocation similarity in diffusion-like models also suggests that it could belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. The focus on improving diversity and accuracy in recommendation models could also place it in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of optimization techniques to achieve optimal recommendation results could also suggest that it belongs to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the use of benchmark datasets and experiments could also suggest that it belongs to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
